        <h3>Dave Cowan</h3>
        <p>My first exposure to a computer was when our family got a Magnavox HeadStart SX running the GeoWorks Ensemble graphic user interface. We had a couple of games including The Manhole and The Secret of Monkey Island. We also had a full set of encyclopedia on CD-ROM! As I recall, this computer had 640K of RAM and a whopping 40MB hard disk. And, it wasn’t compatible with Windows software and third-party support was poor. Needless to say, the future of this line of computers was doomed to failure. Oh, I just remembered we also had a flight simulator called Jet Fighter, which I loved! Ah, the good ol’ days.</p>
    </div>  
