        <h3>Emily Allain</h3>
        <p>My first experience with technology was in the early 2000s.  My mother would bring home the company computer home in the winter from the golf course she worked at;
        without fail we would spend hours playing games endlessly on the computer, to the dismay of my mother.
        The first time we connected to the internet with dial-up internet, our lives were forever changed.</p>

